    Kings Cup

    How to play King\'s Cup
    Grab some friends and some drinks. Players draw a card one at a time and follow the rule until deck is over or players are sufficiently drink. Repeat as many times as necessary. Use the default rules or set your own wacky ones!



    Everyone starts drinking, and can only stop when the person who drew this card stops first.
    Person who drew this card chooses any person to take a drink.
    Person who drew this card takes a drink.
    All the girls playing takes a drink.
    Everyone drinks!
    All the boys playing takes a drink.
    Everyone reaches for the sky. The last person to put their hands up has to drink. 
    Choose one of the players. You and your mate both take a drink.
    Pick any word. Take turns saying words that rhyme with the original word without repeats. First person to pause or screw up drinks!
    Choose a category. Take turns naming an item from the chosen category. First person to pause or screw up drinks!
    Take turns asking questions to each other quickly. First to pause or laughs drinks.
    Say something you have never done. Everyone who has done it takes a drink. Eg, Never have I ever gone skinny dipping.
    Pour a bit of your drink into a cup. Person who draws the last King has to chug the cup.

